      • buildRasterFileFromChrono

        public void buildRasterFileFromChrono(java.lang.String csvRasterChronoName,
                             java.lang.String rasterURL,
                             java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Integer>... bioclimate_to_affinitiesMap)
        Build the data raster from a chronogram file.
        Chronogram format : DATE_COL, X_COL, Y_COL, VALUE1_COL ...
        CSV semicolon separator (;) X_COL and Y_COL must be growing and DATE_COL may be void("";) but not null!
        Parameters:
        csvRasterChronoName -
        rasterURL - where put the raster built
        bioclimate_to_affinitiesMap - used to convert bioclimate to affinities optional Author pamboup 21/06/2013

      • buildChronoFromRasterFile

        public static void buildChronoFromRasterFile(java.lang.String rasterFileName)
        Build a chronogram from a raster file. Ex : We can use excel to build a raster file and this method to transform it to a chronogram. The raster file must be in data_raster/, and the chronogram built will be in data_csv/ in chronogramFromRaster.csv name.
        Parameters:
        rasterFileName - (.txt)
